  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The operating envelope was extended in Q3 2025 to include pediatric patients (body surface area < 0.7 m²) and low-flow neonatal bypass conditions (flow rates 0.3–0.8 L/min); the original validation campaign was conducted exclusively on adult flow regimes (2.0–6.0 L/min). The credibility team has determined that existing validation evidence is considered sufficient to cover the expanded envelope based on geometric similarity arguments and conservative hemolysis model assumptions, without conducting new experimental validation runs for the pediatric sub-population.",
